0in%20Facebook's%20HR%20department%20when%20a%20senior%20executive%20urged%20her%20to%20transfer%20out%20of%20her%20stable%20role%20and%20help%20build%20a%20mobile%20phone%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20took%20the%20risk%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20could%20have%20derailed%20her%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Graham%2C%20who%20later%20became%20a%20C-suite%20executive%20at%20some%20of%20America's%20biggest%20companies%20and%20philanthropies%2C%20now%20views%20that%20risky%20bet%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20moves%20she%20ever%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20felt%20like%20falling%20off%20a%20cliff%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%2C%20now%20the%20founder%20of%20Glue%20Club%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DtwzLDx9iers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELenny%20Rachitsky's%20podcast%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BTaking%20risks%2C%20accepting%20the%20terrible%20fall%20and%20that%20experience%20of%20falling%20has%20been%20more%20than%20worth%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGraham%20described%20the%20experience%20as%20part%20of%20what%20she%20calls%20the%20%26quot%3BJ-curve%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20career%20trajectory%20where%20a%20risky%20move%20leads%20to%20an%20initial%20drop%20before%20eventually%20producing%20outsized%20gains.%20Visually%2C%20she%20describes%20it%20as%20standing%20on%20a%20ledge%2C%20stepping%20off%2C%20sinking%20briefly%2C%20and%20then%20rising%20far%20higher%20than%20where%20you%20started%20%E2%80%94%20just%20like%20the%20shape%20of%20the%20letter%20J.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%2C%20which%20she%20has%20also%20written%20about%20in%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmollyg.substack.com%2Fp%2Fj-curve%3Futm_source%3Dpublication-search%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELessons%3C%2Fa%3E%20Substack%2C%20challenges%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20steady%20career%20ladder%20that%20steadily%20moves%20up%20and%20to%20the%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20climbing%20rung%20by%20rung%20with%20promotions%20every%20two%20to%20five%20years%2C%20Graham%20argues%20that%20some%20of%20the%20most%20valuable%20professional%20growth%20comes%20from%20jumping%20into%20roles%20you%20aren't%20ready%20for%20and%20surviving%20any%20setbacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGraham's%20own%20J-curve%20began%20when%20billionaire%20investor%20and%20%26quot%3BAll-in%26quot%3B%20podcast%20host%20Chamath%20Palihapitiya%2C%20then%20Facebook's%20vice%20president%20of%20growth%2C%20recruited%20her%20to%20help%20develop%20a%20smartphone%2C%20encouraging%20her%20to%20make%20the%20move%20by%20sketching%20out%20the%20J-shaped%20trajectory%20on%20a%20whiteboard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20brought%20her%20on%20despite%20her%20having%20no%20experience%20in%20product%20development%2C%20dropping%20her%20into%20rooms%20filled%20with%20engineers%20and%20phone%20specialists%20with%20deep%20subject%20matter%20expertise.%20She%20recalled%20feeling%20like%20an%20%26quot%3Bidiot%26quot%3B%20for%20much%20of%20her%20first%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223993%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Molly%20Graham%2C%20the%20former%20Facebook%20and%20Google%20executive%2C%20and%20writer%20of%20the%20Lessons%20Substack%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695d7469832e0ef1ead747b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224991%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHeadshot%20of%20Molly%20Graham%2C%20the%20former%20Facebook%20and%20Google%20executive%2C%20and%20writer%20of%20the%20Lessons%20Substack%3Cp%3EMolly%20Graham%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20her%20midyear%20review%2C%20Palihapitiya%20delivered%20what%20Graham%20called%20the%20worst%20performance%20evaluation%20she%20had%20ever%20received.%20But%20the%20new%20experience%20eventually%20expanded%20her%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSlowly%2C%20I%20remember%20I%20had%20been%20doing%20all%20these%20trips%20to%20Taiwan%20because%20we%20were%20actually%20working%20on%20hardware%20and%20I%2C%20at%20some%20point%2C%20came%20back%20from%20Taiwan%20and%20I%20like%20drew%20on%20a%20whiteboard%20for%20him%20the%20layout%20of%20a%20mobile%20phone%2C%20trying%20to%20explain%20to%20him%20kind%20of%20like%20why%20something%20he%20wanted%20to%20do%20was%20not%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20so%20vividly%20remember%20walking%20out%20of%20that%20meeting%20being%20like%2C%20'Oh%20like%20I%20actually%20know%20things.'%20And%20slowly%20then%20over%20the%20following%20three%20years%20I%20became%20an%20expert%20in%20mobile.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalihapitiya%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20phone%20itself%20was%20a%20giant%20failure%20%E2%80%94%20a%20massive%2C%20costly%20failure%20for%20Facebook%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%20told%20Rachitsky%20on%20the%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20was%20not%20a%20failure%20for%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20credits%20the%20experience%20with%20teaching%20her%20that%20she%20could%20operate%20far%20outside%20her%20comfort%20zone%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lesson%20that%20later%20helped%20her%20take%20on%20senior%20leadership%20roles%2C%20including%20serving%20as%20COO%20of%20Quip%2C%20which%20Salesforce%20acquired%20for%20%24750%20million%2C%20and%20overseeing%20operations%20at%20the%20%247.4%20billion%20Chan%20Zuckerberg%20Initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20J-curve%2C%20Graham%20said%2C%20is%20especially%20common%20at%20fast-moving%20companies%20like%20Meta%2C%20Alphabet%2C%20Nvidia%2C%20and%20SpaceX%2C%20where%20leaders%20value%20employees%20who%20are%20willing%20to%20take%20big%20risks%20early%20and%20learn%20quickly.%20In%20those%20environments%2C%20proving%20adaptability%20can%20matter%20more%20than%20checking%20every%20qualification%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20supported%20Graham's%20decision%20at%20the%20time.%20She%20said%20Facebook%20COO%20Sheryl%20Sandberg%2C%20then%20the%20number%2