ret%20phrase%2C%20automatically%20sending%20their%20location%2C%20photos%2C%20and%20audio%20to%20designated%20emergency%20contacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERescuer%20earned%20recognition%20from%20political%20officials%20and%20the%20press.%20What%20mattered%20more%20was%20that%20I%20learned%20that%20code%20written%20from%20my%20bedroom%20could%20help%20someone.%20From%20then%20on%2C%20I%20began%20building%20for%20real%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20answering%20questions%20on%20coding%20forums%2C%20recording%20YouTube%20coding%20tutorials%2C%20and%20writing%20for%20an%20engineering%20blog.%20Over%20time%2C%20my%20answers%20on%20forums%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstack-overflow-crisis-future-of-online-data-ai-world-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStack%20Overflow%3C%2Fa%3E%20reached%20millions%20of%20developers%2C%20which%20only%20deepened%20my%20passion%20for%20continuous%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c399450-107d-433f-8c79-7c1ced6f689b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELiving%20in%20two%20worlds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20still%20one%20thing%20I%20couldn't%20figure%20out%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20many%20downloads%20my%20apps%20received.%20I%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20turn%20an%20app%20into%20a%20real%20business.%20I%20didn't%20understand%20pricing%2C%20customers%2C%20or%20why%20some%20products%20became%20companies%20while%20others%20remained%20weekend%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20was%20deciding%20where%20to%20attend%20college%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20business%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20chose%20UC%20Berkeley's%20M.E.T.%20program%20because%20I%20could%20study%20both%20engineering%20and%20business.%20I%20graduated%20with%20an%20EECS%20(electrical%20engineering%20%26amp%3B%20computer%20science)%20and%20business%20degree%20in%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22de44f0ac-c47a-422c-9e64-09931818000a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20experiment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20when%20ChatGPT%20had%20its%20big%20moment%2C%20I%20asked%20myself%2C%20%3Cem%3EWhat%20if%20I%20could%20just%20talk%20to%20this%20thing%20on%20a%20real%20phone%20line%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20a%20weekend%2C%20I%20hacked%20together%20one%20of%20the%20first%20prototypes%20that%20connected%20ChatGPT%20to%20a%20real%20phone%20number.%20I%20posted%20a%20short%20clip%20and%20a%20tweet%2C%20and%20it%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20was%20not%20ready%20to%20be%20a%20real%20product.%20Latency%20was%20bad.%20Reliability%20was%20fragile.%20The%20models%20made%20strange%20errors.%20But%20that%20experiment%20planted%20a%20question%20in%20my%20mind%20that%20I%20could%20not%20shake%3A%20%3Cem%3EIf%20this%20ever%20became%20good%20enough%2C%20what%20would%20it%20look%20like%20to%20use%20it%20to%20help%20real%20businesses%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22540bc858-98d9-4c4d-9e71-d84b6428350f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaving%20comfort%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20graduation%2C%20I%20had%20offers%20to%20work%20in%20finance%20at%20Citadel%20or%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-engineers-not-on-linkedin-former-meta-employee-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eengineering%20at%20Meta%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'd%20spent%20all%20of%20college%20living%20in%20both%20worlds%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20pick%20just%20one%20side%2C%20but%20I%20chose%20Meta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20shelved%20my%20phone%20experiment%20to%20join%20Meta.%20It%20was%20a%20dream%20setup.%20My%20team%20was%20incredibly%20supportive%2C%20I%20was%20learning%20how%20to%20build%20at%20a%20massive%20scale%2C%20and%20life%20was%20good%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20smart%20colleagues%20to%20the%20famous%20free%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20part%20of%20a%20fintech%20team%20where%20I'd%20push%20one%20line%20of%20code%2C%20and%20millions%20of%20transactions%20would%20be%20affected.%20It%20felt%20less%20like%20a%20corporation%20and%20more%20like%20a%20high-growth%20startup%3B%20I%20was%20given%20incredible%20ownership%20from%20day%20one%20and%20learned%20more%20in%20almost%20two%20years%20than%20I%20expected%20to%20in%20five.%20The%20scale%20was%20exhilarating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20was%20spending%20all%20my%20time%20behind%20the%20code.%20The%20business%20side%2C%20the%20part%20I'd%20learned%20to%20love%20at%20Berkeley%2C%20felt%20far%20away.%20As%20an%20engineer%20at%20a%20big%20company%2C%20there%20was%20no%20clear%20path%20back%20to%20the%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223511eea6-2a5c-4f7b-8e66-673e83d34c88%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20kept%20hearing%20about%20AI%20in%20the%20hallways%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20working%20directly%20on%20AI%2C%20but%20I%20could%20sense%20the%20momentum%20building.%20Every%20few%20months%2C%20the%20models%20improved%20noticeably.%20My%20ChatGPT%20phone%20hack%20stopped%20feeling%20like%20a%20viral%20stunt%20and%20started%20to%20feel%20like%20a%20glimpse%20of%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%20post%20went%20viral%20in%20college%2C%20hundreds%20of%20businesses%20reached%20out%2C%20asking%20for%20a%20solution.%20I%20kept%20thinking%20about%20all%20those%20businesses%2C%20where%20a%20missed%20call%20meant%20a%20missed%20customer.%20I%20knew%20there%20was%20demand%2C%20I%20knew%20nobody%20was%20serving%20them%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20the%20one%20to%20build%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeaving%20wasn't%20easy.%20Meta%20was%20comfortable%2C%20offering%20an%20incredible%20salary%2C%20stock%20refreshers%2C%20and%20interesting%20problems.%20Everyone%20told%20me%20to%20stay%20another%20year%2C%20vest%20more%20equity%2C%20and%20build%20more%20credentials.%20The%20rational%20move%20was%20to%20wait.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20kept%20asking%20myself%2C%20%3Cem%3Eif%20I%20waited%2C%20would%20I%20regret%20it%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20window%20felt%20finite.%20Every%20month%20I%20stayed%20was%20a%20month%20these%20businesses%20were%20not%20being%20served.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22465a1063-4ee7-408f-ad6f-19ee2d33cc9d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20quit%20my%20job%20at%20Meta%20in%20February%202025%20after%201%201%2F2%20years%20at%20the%20company%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20raised%20capital%2C%20moved%20to%20NYC%20from%20California%2C%20and%20began%20building%20Frontdesk.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI'm%20now%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrontdesk%20is%20a%20comprehensive%20AI%20operating%20system%20that%20engages%20with%20customers%20across%20all%20channels%20and%20performs%20real-world%20tasks%2C%20such%20as%20scheduling%20and%20follow-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20work%20in-person%20in%20an%20office%20in%20SoHo.%20Most%20people%20in%20our%20office%20share%20a%20similar%20story%20to%20mine%3B%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flessons-learned-leaving-microsoft-start-own-company-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleft%20Microsoft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Amazon%2C%20or%20Meta%2C%20walking%20away%20from%20good%20salaries%20and%20stock%20options%2C%20because%20they%20believed%20this%20was%20worth%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20lucky%20to%20work%20with%20people%20who%20push%20me%20to%20be%20better%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2225b2293d-2f76-4b01-a217-cb6e1a2a8188%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStill%20pacing%20in%20my%20room%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20nights%2C%20my%20work%20looks%20the%20same%20as%20it%20did%20in%20middle%20school.%20I%20pace%2C%20talk%20into%20a%20phone%2C%20and%20listen%20for%20what%20feels%20off.%20The%20difference%20is%20that%20now%2C%20when%20it%20works%2C%20it%20works%20across%20millions%20of%20calls.%20It's%20the%20same%20instinct%20that%20led%20me%20to%20build%20Rescuer%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20phones%20are%20still%20ringing%2C%20and%20the%20models%20are%20still%20getting%20better.%20I%20know%20where%20I%20want%20to%20be%20while%20that%20ha