thout%20the%20overload%20of%20information%20that%20didn't%20add%20anything%20to%20my%20life%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20nagging%20pressure%20to%20contribute%20to%20it%20%E2%80%94%20I%20felt%20like%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emy%20brain%20was%20freer%20to%20enjoy%20other%20pursuits.%20I%20finished%20more%20books%20(and%20seemed%20to%20better%20process%20what%20I%20read).%20I%20busied%20my%20hands%20with%20crocheting%20instead%20of%20scrolling.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandrew-yang-no-phones-offline-party-nobile-mobile-experience-nyc-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EParties%20became%20more%20fun%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20I%20no%20longer%20mentally%20pre-rehearsed%20the%20photos%20I%20would%20take%20or%20the%20captions%20I%20would%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f4934441-a5fd-4b81-a6ca-aaffc7e36cc1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20got%20creative%20with%20staying%20connected%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cookies%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6945c53904eda4732f2deaaa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20took%20more%20initiative%20in%20inviting%20friends%20over.%3Cp%3EJulia%20Pugachevsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20some%20downsides%20to%20no%20longer%20having%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fappstinence-movement-tech-lovers-dumping-smartphones-age-of-dumb-phones-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eapp%20on%20my%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20generally%20didn't%20miss%20the%20pressure%20to%20post%2C%20it%20was%20frustrating%20not%20to%20have%20that%20option%20on%20the%20desktop%20version.%20When%20someone%20posted%20my%20professional%20work%2C%20all%20I%20could%20do%20was%20%26quot%3Blike%26quot%3B%20the%20post%20and%20move%20on%20instead%20of%20resharing%20it.%20And%20if%20I%20was%20tagged%20in%20a%20friend's%20story%20and%20didn't%20check%20within%2024%20hours%2C%20I%20had%20absolutely%20no%20idea%20what%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20hurdle%20was%20remembering%20birthdays.%20I'd%20grown%20used%20to%20depending%20on%20friends'%20story%20announcements.%20Now%2C%20if%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20look%20like%20an%20ice-cold%20jerk%20on%20everyone's%20special%20days%2C%20I%20had%20to%20get%20creative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20set%20aside%20about%20an%20hour%20one%20day.%20For%20birthdays%20I%20didn't%20already%20have%20memorized%2C%20I%20combed%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-instagram-meme-empire-doing-things-strategy-dms-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eevery%20DM%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20scrolling%20back%20to%20when%20I%20said%20%26quot%3Bhappy%20birthday!%26quot%3B%20and%20wrote%20every%20date%20into%20a%20Notes%20document%20on%20my%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDid%20I%20feel%20slightly%20unhinged%3F%20Yes.%20But%20I%20also%20know%20no%20one's%20ever%20been%20mad%20about%20you%20wishing%20them%20a%20happy%20birthday%20(though%2C%20perhaps%20a%20few%20in%20my%20circle%20were%20a%20little%20spooked).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20pushed%20myself%20to%20get%20over%20my%20lifelong%20fear%20of%20reaching%20out%20first.%20If%20I%20wanted%20to%20feel%20social%20without%20social%20media%2C%20I'd%20need%20to%20be%20a%20little%20more%20outgoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20this%20meant%20writing%20down%20reminders%20to%20text%20people%20when%20I%20thought%20of%20them%2C%20but%20was%20too%20busy%20at%20the%20moment%20to%20reach%20out.%20Other%20times%2C%20I%20offered%20to%20host%20the%20next%20knitting%20club%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-women-forming-book-clubs-to-combat-loneliness-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebook%20club%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20took%20the%20initiative%20to%20coordinate%20group%20plans%20when%20I'd%20usually%20wait%20for%20someone%20else%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20slack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20social%20isolation%20I%20was%20so%20worried%20about%20never%20happened.%20If%20anything%2C%20I%20felt%20more%20social%20because%20I%20was%20prioritizing%20in-person%20interaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd74a341-b760-44b8-888b-82a075793cff%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmbracing%20a%20more%20analog%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cat%20and%20crocheted%20yarn%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6945c4dc04eda4732f2dea9d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20took%20up%20crocheting.%3Cp%3EJulia%20Pugachevsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20got%20a%20taste%20of%20how%20freeing%20being%20offline%20could%20be%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20a%20step%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hated%20how%20often%20I%20woke%20up%20(or%20stayed%20up%20late)%20reading%20the%20news.%20My%20insatiable%20need%20to%20always%20be%20in%20the%20know%20left%20me%20more%20scattered%20and%20irritable.%20So%2C%20I%20cut%20down%20on%20that%2C%20too.%20Halfway%20through%20the%20year%2C%20I%20bought%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrick-gadget-helped-cut-down-my-phone-tiktok-habit-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBrick%20device%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20block%20apps%20like%20my%20email%20or%20the%20internet%20on%20my%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20sometimes%2C%20there%20are%20downsides.%20I've%20missed%20(or%20been%20late%20to)%20big%20life%20updates%20from%20less-close%20friends.%20I've%20drifted%20apart%20from%20a%20few%20others%2C%20with%20whom%20I%20shared%20mostly%20a%20meme-exchanging%20sort%20of%20friendship.%20While%20bittersweet%2C%20it%20has%20also%20helped%20me%20focus%20on%20fewer%2C%20closer%20friends%20than%20an%20unmanageably%20large%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20spend%20my%20mornings%20journaling%2C%20chatti