%20acts%20or%20how%20a%20patient's%20medical%20history%20plays%20into%20their%20condition.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-jagged-edge-work-adoption-chatgpt-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGenerative%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20democratized%20access%20to%20information%20that%20was%20often%20elusive%20and%20expensive%20to%20obtain%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20shifted%20how%20legal%20and%20medical%20professionals%20talk%20to%20people%2C%20and%20what%20people%20expect%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT%20is%20the%20new%20WebMD%20and%20LegalZoom%2C%20turning%20the%20average%20person%20into%20an%20armchair%20expert%20with%20just%20a%20few%20prompts.%20And%20it's%20driving%20the%20real%20experts%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20dispel%20the%20information%20that%20they%20were%20able%20to%20obtain%20versus%20what%20is%20actually%20going%20on%20in%20their%20case%20and%20kind%20of%20work%20backwards%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jamie%20Berger%2C%20a%20family%20law%20attorney%20in%20New%20Jersey.%20For%20example%2C%20Berger%20says%20that%20until%20recently%20most%20people%20knew%20little%20to%20nothing%20about%20the%20legal%20proceedings%20of%20divorce%2C%20and%20would%20come%20to%20the%20attorneys%20seeking%20information.%20Now%2C%20they%20might%20come%20armed%20with%20a%20step-by-step%20gameplan%2C%20but%20it's%20generic%2C%20and%20likely%20not%20the%20best%20fit%20for%20their%20situation.%20Berger%20will%20notice%20after%20emailing%20a%20client%20if%20their%20tone%20suddenly%20changes%2C%20that%20they%20might%20be%20using%20AI%20to%20write%20out%20lengthy%20legal%20strategies%20or%20questions.%20Then%2C%20she%20has%20to%20explain%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20not%20necessarily%20your%20factual%20circumstance%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20address%20their%20various%20points.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20rebuild%20or%20build%20the%20attorney-client%20relationship%20in%20a%20way%20that%20didn't%20used%20to%20exist%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Berger.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20realize%20that%20there's%20so%20many%20offshoots%20along%20the%20way%20that%20it's%20not%20a%20linear%20line%20from%20A%20to%20Z.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20a%20real%20expert%2C%20generative%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-needs-friends-wearable-ai-friend-companion-review-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20chatbots%20speak%20with%20authority%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20can%20be%20far%20more%20persuasive%20than%20reading%20a%20blogpost%20on%20a%20legal%20issue%20or%20summaries%20of%20medical%20conditions%20on%20a%20forum.%20A%20third%20of%20Americans%20said%20yes%20in%20a%202025%20survey%20from%20Survey%20Monkey%20and%20financial%20services%20company%20Express%20Legal%20Funding%20that%20asked%3A%20%26quot%3BWould%20you%20ever%20trust%20ChatGPT%20more%20than%20a%20human%20expert%3F%26quot%3B%2C%20although%20respondents%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20use%20it%20for%20medical%20and%20legal%20advice%2C%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20consult%20it%20for%20educational%20and%20financial%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatbots%20also%20have%20an%20infinite%20amount%20of%20doctors'%20most%20precious%20resource%3A%20time.%20While%20doctors%20are%20pressured%20to%20quickly%20evaluate%20and%20consult%20patients%2C%20chatbots%20are%20always%20available%20and%20designed%20to%20respond%20in%20a%20way%20that%20affirms%20users.%20People%20have%20more%20health%20data%20than%20ever%20from%20wearables%20like%20smartwatches%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Foura-ring-4-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOura%20rings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20they've%20become%20accustomed%20to%20information%20and%20services%20on-demand%2C%20getting%20answers%20from%20doctors%20was%20one%20of%20the%20things%20that%20remained%20behind%20a%20wall%20%E2%80%94%20often%20people%20wait%20months%20for%20appointments%20with%20specialists%20or%20spend%20hours%20fighting%20with%20insurance%20companies%20to%20get%20costs%20covered.%20%26quot%3BThey%20really%20love%20that%20tempo%20of%20being%20able%20to%20know%20that%20ChatGPT%20never%20goes%20away%2C%20never%20goes%20to%20sleep%2C%20never%20says%20no%2C%20never%20says%2C%20'sorry%2C%20your%20list%20is%20too%20long%2C'%26quot%3B%20says%20Hannah%20Allen%2C%20chief%20medical%20officer%20at%20Heidi%2C%20an%20AI%20medical%20scribe%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20also%20acts%20as%20a%20second%20opinion%20without%20the%20wait.%20Heidi%20Schrumpf%2C%20director%20of%20clinical%20services%20at%20teletherapy%20platform%20Marvin%20Behavioral%20Health%2C%20says%20she's%20had%20patients%20return%20after%20a%20counseling%20session%20and%20tell%20her%20that%20they%20took%20her%20input%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-therapy-risks-benefits-boundaries-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20another%20AI%20bot%2C%20and%20that%20they%20trust%20her%20because%20the%20bot%20confirmed%20what%20she%20said.%20But%20Scrumpf%20isn't%20offended%20by%20being%20double-checked.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20great%20that%20they%20have%20the%20access%20to%20a%20quick%20second%20opinion%2C%20and%20then%2C%20if%20it%20doesn't%20agree%20with%20me%2C%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20ask%20me%20better%20questions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202024%20poll%20tracking%20health%20misinformation%20from%20health%20policy%20research%20group%20KFF%20found%20that%2017%25%20of%20US%20adults%20said%20they%20consult%20AI%20chatbots%20at%20least%20once%20a%20month%2C%20but%2056%25%20of%20those%20people%20were%20not%20confident%20that%20the%20info%20from%20the%20AI%20chatbots%20was%20accurate.%20Still%2C%20people%20are%20turning%20to%20ChatGPT%20in%20growing%20numbers.%20%26quot%3BThat%20type%20of%20technology%20does%20want%20to%20encourage%20patients%20to%20continue%20to%20interact%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Allen%20says.%20%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20you%20do%20need%20a%20human%20in%20there%20to%20understand%20the%20nuances%20of%20the%20communication%20and%20the%20softer%20communication%20skills%2C%20and%20the%20unspoken%20communication%20skills%2C%20and%20the%20entire%20medical%20picture%20and%20the%20history.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20detailed%20information%2C%20the%20chatbots%20will%20likely%20give%20generic%20advice.%20But%20supplying%20too%20many%20personal%20details%20is%20also%20a%20risk.%20People%20are%20handing%20over%20their%20entire%20medical%20histories%20to%20ChatGPT%2C%20but%20HIPAA%2C%20the%20federal%20law%20that%20protects%20confidential%20health%20information%2C%20doesn't%20apply%20to%20consumer%20AI%20products.%20There's%20also%20a%20risk%20of%20voiding%20the%20kind%20of%20protections%20people%20get%20from%20the%20attorney-client%20confidentiality%20privilege%20if%20people%20put%20too%20much%20specific%20information%20about%20their%20case%20into%20a%20chatbot%2C%20says%20Beth%20McCormack%2C%20dean%20of%20the%20Vermont%20Law%20School.%20And%2C%20they%20likely%20still%20need%20an%20attorney%20to%20really%20understand%20the%20implications%20of%20AI's%20legal%20advice.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20so%20much%20nuance%20to%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20McCormack%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20fact%20dependent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20OpenAI%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20provide%20comment%20on%20the%20record%20for%20this%20story%2C%20but%20told%20me%20that%20ChatGPT%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20substitute%20legal%20or%20medical%20advice%2C%20but%20act%20as%20a%20complimentary%20resource%20to%20help%20people%20understand%20medical%20and%20legal%20information.%20The%20spokesperson%20also%20said%20the%20company%20is%20trying%20to%20improve%20the%20responses%20of%20its%20models%2C%20and%20that%20it%20takes%20steps%20to%20protect%20personal%20data%20in%20the%20event%20of%20legal%20inquiries.%20OpenAI%20made%20changes%20to%20its%20policies%20last%20fall%2C%20specifying%20that%20users%20cannot%20turn%20to%20ChatGPT%20for%20%26quot%3Bprovision%20of%20tailored%20advice%20that%20requires%20a%20license%2C%20such%20as%20legal%20or%20medical%20advice%2C%20without%20appropriate%20involvement%20by%20a%20licensed%20professional%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20chatbot%20does%20still%20answer%20health-%20and%20law-related%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProfessionals%20aren't%20totally%20against%20their%20patients%20and%20clients%20consulting%20gen%20AI.%20There%20are%20shortages%20of%20doctors%2C%20and%20cases%20that%20require%20hiring%20an%20attorney%20with%20upfront%20money%20that%20people%20don't%20have.%20While%20the%20information%20spit%20out%20by%20AI%20isn't%20always%20perfect%2C%20it%20largely%20makes%20previously%20gate-kept%20legal%20and%20medical%20advice%20accessible%2C%20breaking%20it%20down%20without%20jargon.%20For%20people%20who%20can't%20afford%20upfront%20legal%20costs%2C%20turning%20to%20AI%20can%20be%20helpful%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20says%20Golnoush%20Goharzad%2C%20a%20personal%20injury%20and%20employment%20lawyer%20in%20California.%20People%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Ftech%2Finnovation%2Fai-chatgpt-court-law-legal-lawyer-self-represent-pro-se-attorney-rcna230401%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20ChatGPT%20to%20represent%20themselves%20in%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20act%20as%20a%20stand-in%20therapist%2C%20nutritionist%2C%20or%20physical%20therapist.%20For%20people%20who%20can't%20afford%20lawyers%20and%20are%20facing%20issues%20like%20eviction%20or%20needing%20to%20file%20small%20claims%20cases%2C%20AI%20tools%20have%20helped%20them%20win.%20But%20Goharzad%20says%20she's%20had%20conversations%2C%20sometimes%20with%20friends%2C%20where%20they%20think%20they%20have%20cases%20to%20sue%20landlords%20or%20others.%20She%20asks%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%3F%20That%20doesn't%20even%20make%20any%20sense%2C%20and%20they're%20like%2C%20well%20ChatGPT%20thinks%20it%20makes%20sense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chatbot%20floodgates%20have%20opened%2C%20and%20it's%20too%20late%20for%20professionals%20to%20resist%20them.%20People%20are%20going%20to%20keep%20doing%20their%20own%20research.%20Rather%20than%20fight%20it%2C%20experts%20say%20there's%20room%20to%20recognize%20and%20advise%20people%20on%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20use%20them.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20keep%20as%20clinicians%20in%20the%20back%20of%20our%20mind%20that%20this%20might%20be%20a%20tool%20that%20is%20being%20used%2C%20and%20it%20can%20be%20very%20helpful%2C%20especially%20with%20some%20guidance%20and%20integrating%20it%20into%20our%20treatment%20plans%2C%26quot%3B%20Schrumpf%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20could%20go%20sideways%20if%20we're%20not%20paying%20attention.%26quot%3B%20For%20experts%2C%20the%20time%20has%20come%20to%20assume%20that%20AI%20is%20also%20working%20on%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-new-webmd-doctors-lawyers-medical-advice-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767777421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695c32f764858d02d217c6ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-new-webmd-doctors-lawyers-medical-advice-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chatbots%20are%20making%20amateur%20lawyers%20and%20doctors%20out%20of%20everyone.%20The%20real%20professionals%20have%20second%20opinions%20about%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busine