ng%20to%20%26quot%3Bsqueeze%20another%200.4%25%20of%20margin%26quot%3B%20out%20of%20them.%20They%20were%20ranked%20according%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bdesperation%20score%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20had%20their%20wages%20stolen%20by%20using%20%26quot%3Bpredictive%20modeling%20to%20dynamically%20lower%20the%20base%20pay.%26quot%3B%20Customers%20were%20being%20scammed%20by%20the%20app's%20priority-delivery%20function%2C%20which%20was%20actually%20just%20a%20%26quot%3Bpsychological%20value-add.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20went%20viral%2C%20racking%20up%2087%2C000%20upvotes%20on%20Reddit.%20Commenters%20began%20speculating%20about%20which%20company%20the%20clandestine%20whistleblower%20was%20talking%20about%2C%20with%20many%20eventually%20pointing%20the%20finger%20at%20DoorDash.%20It%20was%20reposted%20on%20dozens%20of%20subreddits%20including%20the%20page%20for%20delivery%20drivers%20where%20hundreds%20of%20commenters%20thanked%20the%20whistleblower%20for%20confirming%20what%20they%20already%20felt.%20A%20screengrab%20of%20the%20post%20garnered%20more%20than%2040%20million%20views%20on%20X%2C%20where%20journalists%2C%20activists%2C%20and%20even%20famous%20actors%20got%20in%20on%20the%20action.%20%26quot%3BA%20perfect%20example%20of%20the%20mindless%20greed%20that%20is%20sucking%20generosity%20and%20kindness%20from%20the%20American%20psyche%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Cleese%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20at%20midnight%20on%20Sunday%2C%20DoorDash's%20CEO%20Tony%20Xu%20stepped%20in%20to%20debunk%20the%20claims%20the%20company%20referred%20to%20Dashers%20as%20%26quot%3Bhuman%20assets%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20it%20tracked%20their%20%26quot%3Bdesperation%20score%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20didn't%20make%20their%20priority%20delivery%20faster.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20DoorDash%2C%20and%20I%20would%20fire%20anyone%20who%20promoted%20or%20tolerated%20the%20kind%20of%20culture%20described%20in%20this%20Reddit%20post%2C%26quot%3B%20Xu%20wrote%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20Monday%2C%20The%20Verge%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2Fnews%2F855328%2Fviral-reddit-delivery-app-ai-scam%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econfirmed%3C%2Fa%3E%20skeptics'%20suspicions%3A%20DoorDash%20Deep%20Throat%20was%20in%20fact%20a%20fraudster.%20In%20an%20attempt%20to%20pull%20a%20fast%20one%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20the%20poster%20had%20AI-generated%20an%20image%20of%20an%20Uber%20Eats%20employee%20badge%20and%20a%20PDF%20that%20purported%20to%20be%20a%20confidential%20study%20that%20would%20corroborate%20the%20redditor's%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20Alex%20Bitter%20was%20also%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20poster.%20In%20a%20series%20of%20messages%20on%20Friday%20and%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20the%20person%20declined%20to%20identify%20themselves%2C%20even%20for%20Business%20Insider's%20verification%20purposes%2C%20or%20get%20on%20the%20phone%20to%20discuss%20their%20post.%20The%20poster%20also%20provided%20files%20that%20had%20a%20high%20likelihood%20of%20being%20AI-generated%2C%20according%20to%20tools%20that%20check%20text%20for%20signs%20of%20AI.%20The%20person%20then%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20more%20questions.%20By%20Tuesday%20evening%2C%20the%20post%20had%20been%20deleted%20on%20Reddit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20were%20so%20many%20people%20duped%3F%20For%20one%2C%20the%20would-be%20whistleblower's%20claims%20were%20not%20completely%20outlandish.%20DoorDash%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fag.ny.gov%2Fpress-release%2F2025%2Fattorney-general-james-secures-1675-million-doordash-cheating-delivery-workers%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFebruary%252024%252C%25202025%2CDoorDash%2527s%2520payment%2520practices%2520going%2520forward.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20faced%20litigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20alleged%20wage%20theft.%20The%20post%20went%20viral%20because%20it%20seemed%20to%20confirm%20what%20we%20already%20suspected%20about%20the%20AI%20that%20permeates%20every%20aspect%20of%20our%20lives%2C%20as%20opaque%20algorithms%20do%20everything%20from%20help%20airlines%20maximize%20prices%20when%20you%20book%20a%20flight%20ticket%20to%20help%20landlords%20jack%20up%20the%20cost%20of%20monthly%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConspiracy%20theories%20are%20a%20type%20of%20rumor%20that%20helps%20us%20make%20sense%20of%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20T.%20Kenny%20Fountain%2C%20an%20academic%20who%20studies%20how%20conspiracy%20theories%20spread%20online.%20%26quot%3BWe%20hear%20constantly%20about%20these%20algorithms%20doing%20these%20bad%20things.%20It%20makes%20sense%20we%20are%20attracted%20to%20conspiratorial%20rumors%20that%20involve%20systems%20that%20seem%20impenetrable%20to%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20human%20desperation%20score%20doesn't%20seem%20all%20that%20farfetched%20when%20a%20little%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20ago%20Meta%20(then%20known%20as%20Facebook)%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Ftechnology-28051930%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFacebook%2520is%2520facing%2520criticism%2520after%2Cwere%2520involved%2520in%2520the%2520study.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaught%20emotionally%20manipulating%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20by%20messing%20with%20the%20kind%20of%20news%20that%20appeared%20on%20our%20feeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20had%20just%20come%20across%20that%20post%20I%20would%20have%20believed%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20AI%20researcher%20Timnit%20Gebru%2C%20who%20in%202020%20blew%20the%20whistle%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.technologyreview.com%2F2020%2F12%2F04%2F1013294%2Fgoogle-ai-ethics-research-paper-forced-out-timnit-gebru%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eracial%20biases%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Google's%20large%20language%20models%2C%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20poster%20is%20a%20fabulist%2C%20Gebru%20explains%2C%20the%20claims%20eerily%20rhymed%20with%20how%20the%20gig%20economy%20actually%20operates.%20This%20past%20fall%2C%20researchers%20at%20the%20AI%20accountability%20nonprofit%20that%20Gebru%20founded%2C%20DAIR%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dair-institute.org%2Fprojects%2Fdriven-down%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleased%20a%20report%20on%20AI%20surveillance%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Amazon%20delivery%20drivers.%20It%20found%20that%20delivery%20drivers%20are%20required%20to%20download%20an%20app%20called%20Mentor%20that%20monitors%20how%20they%20drive%2C%20ranking%20them%20from%20%26quot%3BFantastic%20Plus%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3BPoor.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20app%20doesn't%20take%20into%20account%20real-world%20conditions%20%E2%80%94%20a%20police%20officer%20forcing%20you%20to%20veer%20off%20track%20because%20of%20a%20temporary%20blockade%20or%20a%20child%20following%20a%20runaway%20ball%20across%20the%20road%20forcing%20you%20to%20abruptly%20hit%20the%20brakes.%20All%20of%20which%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20report%20says%2C%20can%20ding%20a%20driver's%20score%20and%20lead%20to%20their%20firing%20if%20they%20fall%20below%20an%20undisclosed%20threshold.%20That's%20just%20one%20of%20the%20apps%20Amazon%20uses%20to%20monitor%20its%20workers%20and%20drive%20them%20to%20such%20extremes%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-drivers-say-peeing-in-bottles-common-despite-company-denials-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20have%20resorted%20to%20urinating%20in%20their%20vans%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20taking%20bathroom%20breaks%20that%20might%20risk%20their%20productivity%20rating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20report%20%E2%80%94%20written%20by%20a%20former%20Amazon%20delivery%20driver%2C%20and%20included%20six%20interviews%20with%20drivers%20working%20for%2010%20different%20providers%20who%20work%20for%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20is%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Bincomplete%20data%20and%20methods%20that%20seem%20designed%20to%20reach%20conclusions%20determined%20from%20the%20start.%26quot%3B%20The%20person%20added%20that%20the%20company%20has%20%26quot%3Ba%20central%20operations%20facility%20that%20makes%20adjustments%20in%20the%20app%20in%20real%20time%20to%20account%20for%20changing%20conditions%2C%20whether%20they%20be%20weather%20or%20otherwise.%26quot%3B%20The%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20my%20follow-up%20on%20what%20Amazon%20considered%20complete%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20last%20year%20DoorDash%20settled%20a%20%2416.65%20million%20algorithmic%20wage%20theft%20lawsuit%20with%20the%20state%20of%20New%20York.%20The%20lawsuit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fag.ny.gov%2Fpress-release%2F2025%2Fattorney-general-james-secures-1675-million-doordash-cheating-delivery-workers%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFebruary%252024%252C%25202025%2CDoorDash%2527s%2520payment%2520practices%2520going%2520forward%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccused%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20using%20tips%20to%20lower%20Dashers'%20base%20pay.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20settlement%2C%20the%20Attorney%20General%20ordered%20DoorDash%20to%20revise%20its%20payment%20practices%20and%20offer%20drivers%20more%20transparency%20about%20the%20breakdown%20of%20their%20paychecks%2C%20but%20DoorDash%20did%20not%20have%20to%20admit%20to%20any%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20for%20comment%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20DoorDash%20directed%20us%20to%20the%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.doordash.com%2Fen-us%2Fnews%2Fhow-doordash-is-different%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20Reddit%20hoax.%20%26quot%3BDasher%20base%20pay%20is%20determined%20by%20three%20factors%20and%20three%20factors%20alone%3A%20time%2C%20distance%2C%20and%20desirability%20of%20a%20given%20offer.%20That's%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20wrote.%20The%20spokesperson%20adds%20that%20the%20settlement%20%26quot%3Bis%20related%20to%20an%20outdated%20pay%20model%20that%20hasn't%20been%20in%20place%20at%20DoorDash%20for%20several%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20now%20we%20have%20become%20so%20accustomed%20to%20reports%20of%20exploitation%20of%20gig%20workers%20that%20it%20is%20almost%20quaint%20to%20think%20back%20to%20the%20mid-2000s%20when%20Big%20Tech%20marketed%20the%20gig%20economy%20as%20unshackling%20workers%20from%20the%20scrutiny%20of%20micromanaging%20bosses%20while%20bringing%20entrepreneurship%20to%20the%20masses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20some%20accounts%2C%20these%20extractive%20practices%20are%20essential%20to%20the%20gig%20economy's%20viability.%20In%20October%2C%20a%20short%20seller%20noted%20that%20even%20a%2010%25%20increase%20in%20Dasher%20wages%20%26quot%3Bwipes%20out%26quot%3B%20the%20entirety%20of%20DoorDash's%202024%20EBITDA.%20Considering%20this%2C%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20last%20year%20alone%20Amazon%2C%20Uber%2C%20and%20DoorDash%20spent%20a%20combined%20%2418.2%20million%20on%20corporate%20lobbying.%20They%20don't%20need%20to%20divert%20a%20%26quot%3BBenefit%20Fee%26quot%3B%20to%20union-busting%20lobbyists%20when%20they're%20already%20doing%20that%20with%20the%20billions%20in%20revenue%20they're%20making%20off%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20meta-level%20irony%20to%20a%20conspiracist%20using%20AI%20to%20stoke%20fears%20about%20how%20AI%20is%20exploiting%20us.%20The%20barrier%20to%20creating%20misinformation%20has%20become%20far%20lower%20while%20detecting%20these%20falsehoods%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsk%20any%20college%20student%20or%20professor%20and%20they'll%20tell%20you%20that%20detection%20software%20is%20notoriously%20bad%20at%20picking%20up%20where%20texts%20were%20written%20by%20AI.%20The%20Verge%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2Fnews%2F855328%2Fviral-reddit-delivery-app-ai-scam%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enoted%20that%20its%20attempts%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20put%20the%20original%20reddit%20post%20through%20AI%20detection%20software%20yielded%20mixed%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20detecting%20fake%20images%20%E2%80%94%20which%20once%20produced%20visible%20watermarks%20and%20quirky%20signatures%20(too%20many%20fingers%20or%20weirdly%20moving%20mouths)%20%E2%80%94%20has%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fshorts%2F3M-BH3tfFc8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enear%20impossible%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20detect%20since%20November%20when%20Google%20released%20Nano%20Banana%20Pro%20and%20allowed%20virtually%20anybody%20to%20create%20perfect-looking%20AI%20generated%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221112%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20badge%20that%20says%20%26quot%3Bsenior%20software%20engineer%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695d695904eda4732f2e93ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20Business%20Insider%20ran%20the%20image%20of%20an%20employee%20badge%20the%20Reddit%20poster%20provided%20through%20Gemini%2C%20the%20software%20said%20the%20image%20was%20likely%20AI-generated.%3Cp%3EReddit%20user%20Trowaway_whistleblow%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%20fabricating%20evidence%20through%20those%20very%20AI%20tools%20is%20what%20led%20reporters%20to%20catch%20the%20conspiracist.%20In%20response%20to%20reporters'%20requests%20to%20back%20up%20the%20claims%2C%20the%20redditor%20sent%20a%20seemingly%20real%20ID%20from%20Uber%20Eats%20with%20their%20identifying%20information%20blacked%20out%20alongside%20another%20official-looking%20report%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emarked%20%26quot%3Bconfidential%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20purported%20to%20corroborate%20the%20information%20in%20the%20reddit%20post.%20They%20were%20caught%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2Fnews%2F855328%2Fviral-reddit-delivery-app-ai-scam%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20AI%20detection%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%20marked%20the%20Uber%20Eats%20ID%20as%20generated%20by%20Google's%20latest%20image-generation%20AI.%20(Uber%20also%20confirmed%20that%20the%20card%20didn't%20match%20the%20actual%20IDs%20used%20by%20the%20company.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Google's%20detection%20software%20can%20only%20tell%20if%20an%20image%20was%20generated%20by%20the%20company's%20AI.%20Had%20the%20faker%20used%20another%20image-generation%20tool%2C%20or%20been%20slightly%20more%20precise%20with%20how%20they%20prompted%20it%2C%20they%20may%20have%20gotten%20away%20with%20it.%20As%20one%20of%20the%20journalists%20that%20debunked%20the%20claims%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.platformer.news%2Ffake-uber-eats-whisleblower-hoax-debunked%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECasey%20Newton%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20writes%2C%20%26quot%3BI'd%20love%20to%20tell%20you%20that%2C%20having%20had%20this%20experience%2C%20I'll%20be%20less%20likely%20to%20fall%20for%20a%20similar%20ruse%20in%20the%20future.%20The%20truth%20is%20that%2C%20given%20how%20quickly%20AI%20systems%20are%20improving%2C%20I'm%20becoming%20more%20worried.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20more%20optimistic%20about%20the%20DoorDash%20dustup.%20First%2C%20the%20post's%20virality%20proves%20that%20we%20aren't%20all%20too%20jaded%20to%20be%20unmoved%20by%20the%20accounts%20of%20exploitation%20that%20have%20become%20essential%20to%20how%20our%20modern%20economy%20functions.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20even%20with%20the%20most%20sophisticated%20AI%20fabrication%20software%20available%20today%2C%20the%20anticipated%20information%20apocalypse%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20successfully%20staved%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20major%20consequence%20of%20AI%20making%20it%20much%20easier%20to%20create%20and%20disseminate%20misinformation%20is%20that%20the%20actual%20work%20of%20truth-seeking%20is%20evermore%20valuable.%20That%20is%20not%20to%20disregard%20the%20crisis%20of%20trust%20in%20the%20news%20industry.%20As%20publications'%20revenue%20from%20social%20media%20companies%20all%20but%20evaporates%2C%20newsroom%20leaders%20would%20do%20well%20to%20reckon%20with%20how%20the%20engagement-bait%20era%20of%20the%202010s%20eroded%20peoples'%20trust%20in%20our%20work.%20Trading%20the%20slow%20and%20meticulous%20work%20of%20rigorous%20fact-checking%20in%20favor%20of%20pushing%20quick%20content%20for%20likes%20and%20retweets%20will%20not%20be%20a%20sustainable%20business%20practice%20in%20an%20era%20of%20sophisticated%20dupes%20and%20falsehoods.%20DoorDash%20Deep%20Throat%20is%20the%20latest%20case%20study%20for%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20might%20never%20know%20why%20this%20redditor%20spent%20the%20weekend%20hatching%20an%20elaborate%20plan%20to%20fool%20the%20internet.%20But%20if%20the%20information%20environment%20of%20the%20foreseeable%20future%20is%20flooded%20with%20viral%20hoaxes%2C%20or%20if%20the%20ubiquity%20of%20such%20misinformation%20gives%20powerful%20figures%20the%20ability%20to%20cry%20fake%20news%20when%20faced%20with%20authentic%20leaks%2C%20the%20institutions%20that%20strive%20to%20foster%20the%20public's%20trust%20have%20the%20most%20to%20gain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAdditional%20reporting%20by%20Alex%20Bitter.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Ftekendra-parmar%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ETekendra%20Parmar%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20former%20features%20editor%20at%20Business%20Insider.%20He%20has%20also%20worked%20at%20Rest%20of%20World%2C%20Time%2C%20Fortune%2C%20Harper's%20Magazine%2C%20and%20The%20Nation.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-deep-throat-scam-lays-bare-new-era-untruthiness-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767777061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695d4ada64858d02d217d5d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-deep-throat-scam-lays-b